HEADWORD: Legionary
<hw>Le"gion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(-⟦asl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>legionarius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>l⟦eacute⟧gionnaire</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Belonging to a legion; consisting of a legion or legions, or of an
indefinitely great number; <as>as, <ex>legionary</ex> soldiers; a
<ex>legionary</ex> force.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>legionary</xex>
body of error.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Legionary</ent>⟦br⟧

